  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-02-28",
    "date": "2023-04-11T21:45:40Z",
    "text": "Confederate Monument Removal Act\n\nThis bill prohibits a state from providing for display in National Statuary Hall of the U.S. Capitol a statue of a person who voluntarily served with the Confederate States of America. The bill also provides funding for removing any statue currently on display that depicts such a person and outlines procedures for returning and replacing such statutes."
